er<span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'lucid'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"dimer-highlight-code-line\"><span class=\"token function-variable function\">model</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'App/Models/User'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Finally, we have deprecated the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Env.getOrFail"}]},{"type":"text","value":" method in favor of the Env validations. You just need to find its usages and replace it with "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Env.get"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to avoid getting deprecation warnings."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using Japa as your test runner? "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#using-japa"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Here are the instructions"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to upgrade the test runner to run tests using the Typescript source directly."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"in-memory-typescript-compilation"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#in-memory-typescript-compilation","aria-hidden":true},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"className":["icon","icon-link"]},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"In-memory Typescript compilation"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I am not a big fan of build tools or adding an additional step to prepare my code for getting executed. However, when using Typescript there is no way to escape the process of compiling Typescript to JavaScript since v8 is meant to run Javascript only."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Initially, we did add a build step in which we compile Typescript to JavaScript before starting the development server."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In the following screenshot, the first five steps involve compiling the code to Javascript and copying some files to the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"build"}]},{"type":"text","value":" folder to start the HTTP server."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"src":"https://res.cloudinary.com/adonis-js/image/upload/v1603450209/adonisjs.com/serve.png"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Even though the process seems logical, it has a lot of rough edges that will bite you once in a while. Many users created GitHub discussion threads lately expressing:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I have updated my migrations code and it is not picked up by the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"node ace migration:run"}]},{"type":"text","value":" command"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I am getting the error "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"node ace make:migration"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is not a command"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"and so on"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All this confusion is a result of a stale "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"build"}]},{"type":"text","value":" folder and you have to make sure that one process is always running to keep the build output up to date."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"lets-do-something-better"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#lets-do-something-better","aria-hidden":true},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"className":["icon","icon-link"]},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Let's do something better"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I have been banging my head lately to find some alternative which feels more natural and intuitive over this additional build step, and voila there is "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/TypeStrong/ts-node"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ts-node"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ts-Node is a library to run typescript code directly without transpiling it first. But, I decided to "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"not use it"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and instead "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/adonisjs/require-ts"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"write my version of it"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for the following reasons."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I wanted to avoid Type checking completely. No one looks at the terminal for checking the typescript errors. We all rely on our editors to report the errors and hence there is no need to slow down the compilation process."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use aggressive caching to make subsequent runs faster. TS node doesn't support caching as of today. There are some open issues to add it, but since they do a lot more than "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"@adonisjs/require-ts"}]},{"type":"text","value":" they have to handle all other use cases as well."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Creating API for the watchers to invalidate the cache for the changed/updated files."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"how-in-memory-compilation-works"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#how-in-memory-compilation-works","aria-hidden":true},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"className":["icon","icon-link"]},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"How in-memory compilation works?"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now that you are aware of the reasons for not using the ts-node, let's expand upon how in-memory compilation works and also the entire cache mechanism built to make subsequent runs faster."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Node.js has a thing called "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://gist.github.com/jamestalmage/df922691475cff66c7e6"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"require extensions"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Using this you can tell Node to call a function anytime a file with the given extension is required. Babel, ts-node, and many other libraries use this to hook into the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"require"}]},{"type":"text","value":" lifecycle of Node.js"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Typescript compiler API has a "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/Microsoft/TypeScript/wiki/Using-the-Compiler-API#a-simple-transform-function"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"transpileModule"}]},{"type":"text","value":" method. You can pass the typescript source code as a string to this method and it will return you the compiled Javascript."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, if you combine the above two you can compile the typescript code on the fly. However, typescript does take some time to compile the code and this can make restarts slow. Let's visualize a standard development workflow."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You run the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"node ace serve --watch"}]},{"type":"text","value":" command."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"AdonisJS hooks into the require lifecycle and take control of compiling the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"typescript"}]},{"type":"text","value":" files."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As your application is getting ready all the source code imported using the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"import"}]},{"type":"text","value":" statement is getting compiled on the fly."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next, you make some modifications to a given file."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The file watcher is notified and it restarts the HTTP server and hence all the previously compiled code is destroyed since it was in memory."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You have changed just one file and now everything needs to be re-compiled again. BUMMER!"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"using-cache"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#using-cache","aria-hidden":true},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"className":["icon","icon-link"]},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Using cache"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"On-disk caching is the only solution to avoid re-compiling the entire project after a single file change. The following are the steps we perform for caching."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Begin by generating the md5 hash of the file contents and use the hash as the filename to save the compiled contents on the disk."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next time, if the hash is still the same we read the compiled source from the disk instead of using the typescript compiler API. To our surprise, generating the hash + reading file from the disk is faster than re-compiling the code in many cases."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If the hash is different we just ignore the cache and use the typescript compiler API."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The term "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ignore the cache"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is important here. Since we don't remove the old cache there is going to be a time when the cache will end taking a lot of disk space."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To counter that, we "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/adonisjs/require-ts/blob/develop/index.ts#L43"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"expose an API"}]},{"type":"text","value":" from the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"@adonisjs/require-ts"}]},{"type":"text","value":" module that the file watchers can use to clear the entire cache or remove a single file from it."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"result"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#result","aria-hidden":true},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"className":["icon","icon-link"]},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Result"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Finally, we end up with a development workflow that can run Typescript source code directly and uses cache for faster restarts."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"div","props":{"className":["embed","video"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"video","props":{"controls":true},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"source","props":{"src":"https://res.cloudinary.com/adonis-js/video/upload/v1603462870/adonisjs.com/quick-restart_cgjdfa.mp4","type":"video/mp4"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"validating-environment-variables"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#validating-environment-variables","aria-hidden":true},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"className":["icon","icon-link"]},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Validating environment variables"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Environment variables play a very important role in our applications. Moreover, environment variables are not in control of our source code and we heavily rely on the outside factors to provide the correct values. For example:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using a plain text file "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".env"}]},{"type":"text","value":" during development."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Using the control panel of cloud services lik